TopicTitle: BUG: Crash after successful recue in orbit.

Articles.Content:
I recued 1 kerbal from orbit, landed and after click to recover vessel the game crashed.

After I opened it again the kerbal that I recue joined my crew but the contract didnt complete and I didnt get the reward

Not sure why it crashed, but you can force the game to complete the contract by opening the debug menu (ALT+F12). Click on "Contracts," find your rescue contract, and click "Com" (for Complete).

If you still have the crash logs, uploading the output_log.txt could help us figure out what caused it (so that maybe it can be prevented in the future).

Cheers,

~Claw

Thank you for that Debug hint, solved my contract issue.

It's not an output_log.txt, it's an error.log but it shows the problem well enough - I believe you've run out of memory.

The log file can be found in the following places:

Windows: KSP_win\KSP_Data\output_log.txt -OR- KSP_win64\KSP_x64_DATA\output_log.txt (depending on which used)

- In case you installed KSP into a Windows protected directory (C:\Users, C:\Program Files or C:\Windows\ and their subfolders) the output log file may be stored in the folder called C:\Users\[username]\Appdata, this folder is usually hidden so you should enable the view hidden folders option (more information). Note that for the demo you should find the output_log.txt file located in the KSP_Data folder.

- Steam users should right click KSP in Steam, click on Properties, then in the Properties box, click Local Files, then Browse Local Files.

Mac OSX: Open Console, on the left side of the window there is a menu that says 'files'. Scroll down the list and find the Unity drop down, under Unity there will be Player.log Aka Files>~/Library/Logs>Unity>Player.log

Linux: The log is written to /home/user/.config/unity3d/Squad/Kerbal Space Program/Player.log

That occur again a couple of times.

It should be a memory problem indeed because looking at the task manager it says KSP 'eats' 2.5+ Gbs of RAM. That's insane.

Hope they can fix this memory problem in the future.

Thanks guys.
